          "birdseye": "1882 Flett",
          "map": "1882 Lawrence",
          "text": "City Hall was then moved to the 14th and Larimer [K on map] location in 1883. [...] The building took 15 months to construct, was designed by W. K. Nichols, and cost about $300,000.  The original building was four floors with a bell tower and a copula.  On Novermber 30, 1901 it caught fire.  The fire burned the fourth floor.  It was rebuilt with a flat roof.",
